To turn this mock-up into a colorful website, you can use HTML and CSS to create a layout and design for the page. You can use JavaScript to replace the jokes with actual jokes, fetched from a database or an API. Here's a basic example of how you could structure the HTML and CSS for the page:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>My Joke Website</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #f2f2f2;
    }
    .joke-container {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .joke {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="joke-container">
    <div class="joke">
      <p>Isaac, a bat joke:</p>
      <p>Why did the bat go to the doctor?</p>
      <p>Because he was feeling batty!</p>
    </div>
    <div class="joke">
      <p>Joke 2:</p>
      <p>Why did the tomato turn red?</p>
      <p>Because it saw the salad dressing!</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script>
    // Replace the jokes with actual jokes using JavaScript
    // You can fetch the jokes from a database or an API
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```
This is just a basic example, and you can further enhance the design and functionality of the website by adding more elements, animations, and interactivity.

To create a colorful and interactive website with a real joke replacing the mock-up joke, you can use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Here's a basic outline of the steps:

1. Create a new HTML file and add a container for the joke, such as a `<div>` element.
```html
<div id="joke-container">
  <p id="joke"></p>
</div>
```
1. Add a JavaScript file to the HTML file and create a function to fetch a random joke from a joke API, such as the one provided by <https://api.chucknorris.io/jokes/random>.
```javascript
async function fetchJoke() {
  const response = await fetch('https://api.chucknorris.io/jokes/random');
  const data = await response.json();
  return data.value;
}
```
1. In the HTML file, add a button to trigger the joke fetching and display the joke in the container.
```html
<button id="joke-button">Get a joke</button>
```
1. Add a CSS file to style the joke container and button.
```css
#joke-container {
  background-color: #ffcc00;
  padding: 20px;
  border-radius: 10px;
  text-align: center;
}

#joke {
  font-size: 24px;
  color: #000;
}

#joke-button {
  background-color: #ffcc00;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border-radius: 10px;
  font-size: 20px;
  cursor: pointer;
}
```
1. In the JavaScript file, add an event listener to the button to fetch the joke and update the container with the fetched joke.
```javascript
const jokeButton = document.getElementById('joke-button');
jokeButton.addEventListener('click', fetchJoke);
```
1. Finally, update the HTML file to include the JavaScript file and the joke container.
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>My Joke Website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="joke-container">
      <p id="joke"></p>
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
```
With these steps, you can create a colorful and interactive website that displays a real joke when the user clicks the button.
